PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1891118
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 101
IS  - 2
SP  - 323
EP  - 339
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines the impact of changes in gasoline price expectations on the market values of used automobiles. An asset model of automobile valuation is used to relate year-to-year changes in market values to changes in the present discounted value of gasoline expenses. Econometric evidence from data covering the years 1972 through 1981 substantially confirms the hypothesis of the model that a gasoline price shock causes relative price changes across automobile types in proportion to the differences in their rates of fuel consumption.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1891118
ER  - 



